          "text": "eateries = 食肆；餐飲場所\nExample: Eateries should not be turned into long-stay tutorial venues.\n（食肆不應被變成長時間逗留的補習場所。）\n\ncoffee shops and fast-food restaurants = 咖啡店和快餐店\nExample: Coffee shops and fast-food restaurants are designed mainly for customers who want meals, drinks and short breaks.\n（咖啡店和快餐店主要是為想用餐、喝飲品和短暫休息的顧客而設。）\n\ncommercial dining space = 商業用餐空間\nExample: Commercial dining space should not be occupied for private educational activities for hours.\n（商業用餐空間不應被私人教育活動長時間佔用。）\n\nrestaurant owners = 餐廳東主；食肆經營者\nExample: Restaurant owners may lose business when tables are occupied by non-dining groups.\n（當餐桌被非用餐群體佔用時，餐廳東主可能會失去生意。）\n\nfrontline staff = 前線員工\nExample: Frontline staff often have to deal tactfully with customers who stay too long.\n（前線員工往往要婉轉處理逗留太久的顧客。）\n\nordinary customers / other patrons = 普通顧客 / 其他顧客\nExample: Ordinary customers may struggle to find seats during busy hours.\n（普通顧客在繁忙時間可能難以找到座位。）\n\ndiners = 食客；用餐人士\nExample: A restaurant exists to serve diners efficiently.\n（餐廳的存在是為了有效率地服務食客。）\n\nshared space = 共享空間\nExample: Shared space should be used with consideration for others.\n（共享空間應該在顧及他人的情況下使用。）\n\navailable tables = 可用餐桌；空桌\nExample: New customers may leave when there are no available tables.\n（當沒有空桌時，新顧客可能會離開。）\n\ncrowded dining areas = 擁擠的用餐區\nExample: Families may have to carry trays around crowded dining areas.\n（家庭顧客可能要端著托盤在擁擠的用餐區四處尋找座位。）\n\ncorner table = 角落餐桌\nExample: A corner table should not be treated as a substitute for a real classroom.\n（一張角落餐桌不應被視為真正課室的替代品。）\n\na cheap drink = 一杯便宜飲品\nExample: Buying a cheap drink does not justify occupying a restaurant table for hours.\n（買一杯便宜飲品並不能合理化長時間佔用餐廳桌子。）"
