          "text": "推理路線\nCoffee shops and fast-food restaurants should not be treated as long-stay tutorial venues\n咖啡店和快餐店不應被當作長時間補習場地\n→ the practice is unfair to businesses\n→ 這做法對商戶不公平\n→ it is inconsiderate to other customers\n→ 它對其他顧客不體貼\n→ it is educationally misguided\n→ 它在教育上方向錯誤\n→ restaurants can introduce clearer seating policies\n→ 餐廳可以推出更清晰的座位政策\n→ tutors should act more responsibly\n→ 補習老師應更負責任\n→ schools and government should expand affordable study spaces\n→ 學校和政府應增加可負擔學習空間\n→ students can learn somewhere suitable without inconveniencing the public\n→ 學生可以在適合地方學習而不妨礙公眾\n→ a corner table and a cheap drink should not replace a real classroom\n→ 一張角落餐桌和一杯便宜飲品不應取代真正課室\n分析\nThe conclusion works well because it restates the writer’s judgement and then offers practical steps. It ends with a strong concrete image: “a corner table and a cheap drink” versus “a real classroom.” This image neatly summarises the whole essay’s argument that improvised space is not the same as proper educational provision.\n（結論有效，因為它重申作者判斷，然後提出實際步驟。它以強烈具體畫面作結：「一張角落餐桌和一杯便宜飲品」對比「真正課室」。這畫面精準總結全文：臨時湊合的空間不等於真正教育配套。）"
